An anonymous reader writes "When Yahoo!'s Jeremy Zawodny recently asked
[0]What the heck is Web 2.0 anyway? he received a set of responses
reminiscent of those garnered by The Register back in 2005, which
famously concluded, based on its readers' responses, that [1]Web 2.0 was
made up of 12% badger's paws, 6% JavaScript worms, and 26% nothing.
Nonetheless, as Social Computing (SoC) widens and deepens its footprint,
another Jeremy — Jeremy Geelan — has asked if we are [2]witnessing the
death of 'Personal' Computing. SoC, Geelan notes, has already become an
[3]academic [4]field of study. But perhaps Social Computing too is just
badger's paws?"

