| Disney Says, You WILL Watch the Ads                                |
|   from the step-away-from-the-remote dept.                         |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 08, @13:59 (Television)         |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/08/1654258              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

smooth wombat writes "ABC and ESPN, both owned by Disney, have struck a
deal with cable operator Cox Communications to offer hit shows and
football games on demand, but with the condition that [0]Cox disable the
fast-forward feature that allows viewers to skip ads. This is the first
agreement of its kind. It only applies to Cox's video-on-demand service
and will not affect viewers using DVRs to fast-forward through ads. The
companies will also test technology that will place ads in shows based on
ZIP Codes and geographic area, and 'freshen' the ads with new ones every
few days."

