| Europe's Galileo Program In Serious Trouble                        |
|   from the tell-me-again-why-we-are-building-this dept.            |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 08, @14:38 (Space)              |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/08/1731223      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

elrous0 writes "Various news outlets are reporting that Europe's Galileo
program is [0]facing a serious financial and technical crisis and [1]may
be permanently stalled. The European program, designed to be a superior
answer to the US's GPS — and, more critically, not controlled by the US —
has faced numerous hurdles since its inception. To date the Galileo
program has succeeded in launching only one of its 30 planned satellites
and has been beset by delays and cost overruns. Apparently, squabbling
between the eight companies in the consortium behind the project is
responsible for many of the problems. The project is now threatened with
an EU takeover. But some [2]doubt that even an infusion of EU capital can
save the flagging program."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/08/1731223

