| Warner Brothers Pulls Canadian Previews                            |
|   from the camcorders-eh dept.                                     |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 08, @15:18 (Movies)             |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/08/1816249          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

A number of readers let us know that Reuters and others are reporting
that Warner Brothers is [0]canceling movie previews in Canadian theaters,
starting with Oceans Thirteen. A Warner VP said, "Within the first week
of a film's release, you can almost be certain that somewhere out there a
Canadian copy will show up." Recently, the International Intellectual
Property Association [1]placed Canada on its Priority Watch List, along
with the likes of Argentina, China, Russia, Turkey, and Venezuela. This
community knows, thanks to Michael Geist, that [2]the claim is mostly
ficiton.

