| Proposed Legislation Is Mooninite Fallout                          |
|   from the against-stupidity-the-gods-themselves dept.             |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 08, @18:08 (Politics)           |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/08/190220      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

theantipop writes "Ars Technica has a story about the [0]Terrorist Hoax
Improvements Act, a bill introduced recently by the Senate. The bill aims
to 'amend the federal criminal code to include a number of new clauses
meant to up the ante on wasting government resources. The amendments
include extensions to the prohibitions on the spread of false information
and mailing threats, increases to maximum prison terms, and allowances
for civil suits so that local and federal governments can attempt to
recoup expenses related to an incident.' This is undoubtedly a reaction
to the [1]Great Mooninite Scare of 2007."

